President Biden has declared a state of emergency in Mississippi due to the conditions resulting from Hurricane Ida. This declaration authorizes the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to coordinate disaster relief efforts and provide assistance to alleviate the hardships caused by the emergency. FEMA is authorized to mobilize equipment and resources as needed, and emergency protective measures will be funded at 75% by the federal government. Thomas J. McCool has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.